            <h1>12th Marksheet Documentation</h1>
            <p>Higher Secondary Certificate - Education Board</p>
        </div>
    </header>

    <main class="container">
        <section class="doc-overview">
            <div class="card">
                <img src="/images/<%= data.image_data %>" alt="12th Marksheet Sample" class="doc-logo">
                <div class="doc-meta">
                    <p><strong>Issuing Authority:</strong> Respective Education Board (CBSE/State Board)</p>
                    <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Higher education admissions, employment, government exams</p>
                    <p><strong>Validity:</strong> Lifetime (can be reissued if lost)</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="application-process">
            <h2><i class="fas fa-list-ol"></i> Step-by-Step Application Process</h2>
            
            <div class="process-steps">
                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-number">1</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h3>Identify Your Education Board</h3>
                        <p>Determine which board issued your marksheet:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>CBSE:</strong> For Central Board schools</li>
                            <li><strong>State Boards:</strong> Like Maharashtra, UP, Tamil Nadu etc.</li>
                            <li><strong>ISC:</strong> For ICSE affiliated schools (Class 12)</li>
                            <li><strong>NIOS:</strong> For National Institute of Open Schooling</li>
                            <li>Check your school's affiliation certificate if unsure</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-number">2</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h3>Gather Required Information</h3>
                        <p>Essential details needed for application:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Full name (as per school records)</li>
                            <li>Parents' names</li>
                            <li>Complete school name and address</li>
                            <li>Year of passing and examination roll number</li>
                            <li>Registration number and stream (Science/Commerce/Arts)</li>
                            <li>Subject combinations and practical exam details</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-number">3</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h3>Choose Application Type</h3>
                        <p>Select the appropriate application method:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Original Collection:</strong> From school (for recent pass-outs)</li>
                            <li><strong>Duplicate Marksheet:</strong> For lost/damaged certificates</li>
                            <li><strong>Migration Certificate:</strong> For university admissions</li>
                            <li><strong>Digital Copy:</strong> Through board portals/DigiLocker</li>
                            <li><strong>Attestation:</strong> For foreign education/employment</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-number">4</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h3>Apply for Duplicate Marksheet</h3>
                        <p>Procedure for lost/damaged certificates:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>File FIR at local police station (for lost marksheet)</li>
                            <li>Get affidavit notarized (mentioning reason for duplicate)</li>
                            <li>Obtain application form from board office/website</li>
                            <li>Attach: FIR copy, affidavit, ID proof, address proof</li>
                            <li>Include 2-4 passport photos (as per board requirement)</li>
                            <li>Pay fees (varies by board, typically ₹500-1000)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-number">5</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h3>Submit Application</h3>
                        <p>Submission process:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Online:</strong> For CBSE/State Boards with digital portals</li>
                            <li><strong>Offline:</strong> At regional board office or through school</li>
                            <li><strong>Special Cases:</strong> NRIs can apply through Indian embassies</li>
                            <li>Get acknowledgment receipt with tracking number</li>
                            <li>Processing time: 15-45 days (varies by board)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-number">6</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h3>Obtain Digital Marksheet</h3>
                        <p>For instant access:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>CBSE: <a href="https://cbse.digitallocker.gov.in/" target="_blank">DigiLocker</a> or <a href="https://results.cbse.nic.in/" target="_blank">results.cbse.nic.in</a></li>
                            <li>State Boards: Respective board websites</li>
                            <li>Create account on DigiLocker (linked with Aadhaar)</li>
                            <li>Search using roll number and year of passing</li>
                            <li>Download digitally signed marksheet (legally valid)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-number">7</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h3>Receive Physical Copy</h3>
                        <p>Delivery options:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>School Collection:</strong> 4-8 weeks after results</li>
                            <li><strong>Postal Delivery:</strong> For duplicate applications</li>
                            <li><strong>Board Office Pickup:</strong> For urgent cases</li>
                            <li>Verify all details (name, marks, subjects) upon receipt</li>
                            <li>Report discrepancies immediately to board authorities</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="video-guide">
            <h2><i class="fas fa-video"></i> Official Tutorial Video</h2>
