        <section class="important-notes">
            <h2><i class="fas fa-exclamation-circle"></i> Important Information</h2>
            <div class="notes-grid">
                <div class="note-card">
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-rupee-sign"></i> Fee Structure</h3>
                    <p>CBSE Duplicate: ₹500 + postal charges<br>
                    State Boards: ₹300-1000<br>
                    Migration Certificate: ₹250<br>
                    Attestation: ₹200-500 per document</p>
                </div>
                <div class="note-card">
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-file-contract"></i> Document Requirements</h3>
                    <p>FIR (for lost marksheet)<br>
                    Notarized affidavit<br>
                    School leaving certificate<br>
                    ID proof (Aadhaar/PAN/Passport)<br>
                    4 passport photos (white background)</p>
                </div>
                <div class="note-card">
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-phone-volume"></i> Board Contacts</h3>
                    <p>CBSE Helpline: <strong>1800-11-8002</strong><br>
                    Maharashtra Board: <strong>022-22041800</strong><br>
                    UP Board: <strong>0532-2467631</strong><br>
                    NIOS: <strong>011-40769000</strong></p>
                </div>
                <div class="note-card">
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-clock"></i> Processing Time</h3>
                    <p>Duplicate Marksheet: 20-45 days<br>
                    Migration Certificate: 10-15 days<br>
                    Digital Copy: Instant (if available)<br>
                    Corrections: 30-60 days</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="faq-section">
            <h2><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>Is digital 12th marksheet valid for college admissions?</h3>
                <p>Yes, digitally signed marksheets from official board portals or DigiLocker are legally valid as per UGC and AICTE guidelines for all admissions.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>Can I get my 25-year-old 12th marksheet reissued?</h3>
                <p>Yes, all education boards maintain permanent archives. You can apply for duplicate marksheet by submitting required documents and fees.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>What if there are errors in my original marksheet?</h3>
                <p>Contact your school immediately within 6 months of issue. The school will initiate correction process with the board. For older certificates, you may need to apply for duplicate with correct details.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>How to get marksheet attested for foreign universities?</h3>
                <p>First get it attested by the issuing board, then by HRD Ministry, and finally by the concerned embassy. Some states have single-window systems for attestation.</p>
            </div>
        </section>
